properties.areaDesc: Central U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca; West Entrance U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 25 at 8:59AM PST until January 26 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...East winds 20 to 30 kt becoming west southwest 15 to 25
knots Sunday.

* WHERE...West Entrance U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca and
Central U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...From 1 AM to 6 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher at the West Entrance are expected
to produce hazardous wave conditions to small craft.
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels should avoid navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 6 PM PST SUNDAY
